      "text": "<h3> Entropy + Algebra + Topology = ?</h3>\n<p>Wed, Jul 28, 2021</p>\n<p>Today I'd like to share some math connecting ideas from information theory, algebra, and topology. It's all in a new paper I've recently uploaded to the arXiv (https://arxiv.org/abs/2107.09581), which describes a correspondence between Shannon entropy and functions on topological simplices that obey a version of the Leibniz rule from Calculus. The paper is short &#148; just 11 pages!Even so, I thought it'd be nice to stroll through some of the surrounding ideas here on the blog. [Read more on Math3ma.]- [https://www.math3ma.com/blog/entropy-algebra-topology math3ma.com]</p>\n<hr>"
